Sennosuke: You telling me what to do now?

Yang-Tai: Stop right there!

Yang-Tai: You're going too far this time! You won't stop, even for a child!

Yang-Tai: The Kai-Tai Group runs its own emergency relief fund. Come on then, how much does she owe?

Yang-Tai: Here! Take this receipt and exchange it at our lodge.

Yang-Tai: All right, everything's okay. Don't be afraid now.
Baa Baa: Thank... thank you.
Yang-Tai: You're welcome. Elders should look out for the younger generation.
Baa Baa: But'cha didn't even ask why I needed the money in the first place...

Baa Baa: ...I don't have a home. I... I've always been all alone...
Yang-Tai: Oh... I see. Well then, would you like to come back to our group's lodge with me?
Baa Baa: Whaaat?! I knew it! Ya only bought me out so I'd be forever in yer debt instead, didn'tcha!
Yang-Tai: Well now... I don't remember saying that.
Baa Baa: What are you laughing at...?
Yang-Tai: Nothing. You can look at it that way if you want, too. How about the two of us do a little business together, then?
Baa Baa: ...I guess having a patron... I mean, having a place to stay... wouldn't be so bad.
Yang-Tai: Wonderful. Come with me.
Baa Baa: Wait a tick.
Baa Baa: Let's draw us up a contract, so we won't get into any trouble later.
Yang-Tai: Aren't you a sharp businesswoman, heheh. Let me see... How do I read this name here...?
Baa Baa: Baa~ You know, like, Baa Baa.
Yang-Tai: What a lovely smile you've got.
Baa Baa: Baa?!
Yang-Tai: The first rule of the Kai-Tai Group isâ€”Greet everyone with a smile. It takes a nice toothy grin to get rich, you know~
Baa Baa: Greet everyone with a smile, huh~
